:{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n**Module:** cmd\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\n<!-- TODO: Describe the purpose and motivation for this change -->\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n<!-- TODO: List what is in scope -->\n\n### 不包含\n\n<!-- TODO: List what is out of scope -->\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775849593414,"end":1775849593433}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849594793,"sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","part":{"id":"prt_d78e25ad5001n5Jp0fW154889s","messageID":"msg_d78e24cef0018H39ki6ye8nBZ4","sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_233200afa0e84cbcac8c05fa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: AgentCube 由 4 个独立的 Go 二进制组成，各自承担明确的运行时职责：\n8: \n9: | Binary | Package | Role | Pattern |\n10: |--------|---------|------|---------|\n11: | `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Sandbox CR 控制器，监听 Sandbox 资源变化并调谐 Pod 生命周期 | controller-runtime reconciler |\n12: | `picod` | `cmd/picod` | 沙箱内守护进程，提供代码执行 + 文件管理 API | standalone HTTP server (gin) |\n13: | `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | 沙箱编排 API 服务：创建/删除/列表/状态/TTL 续期 + GC 清理 | HTTP API + informer-based reconciler |\n14: | `router` | `cmd/router` | 反向代理网关：JWT 鉴权 → session 查找 → 请求转发到沙箱 Pod | HTTP reverse proxy + informer-driven routing |\n15: \n16: 四者通过 Kubernetes API（CRD + informers）和共享 store（Redis/Valkey）协同，无直接进程间通信。\n17: \n18: ### 1.2 Package Layout\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── agentd/\n23: │   └── main.go                  — controller-runtime manager + Sandbox reconciler\n24: ├── picod/\n25: │   └── main.go                  — ParseFlags → NewServer → Run\n26: ├── workloadmanager/\n27: │   └── main.go                  — [TODO] CLI entry point\n28: └── router/\n29:     └── main.go                  — [TODO] CLI entry point\n30: \n31: pkg/\n32: ├── agentd/                      — agentd business logic (existing)\n33: │   ├── reconciler.go\n34: │   ├── reconciler_test.go\n35: │   └── const.go\n36: ├── picod/                       — picod business logic (existing)\n37: │   ├── server.go\n38: │   ├── config.go\n39: │   ├── types.go\n40: │   ├── auth.go\n41: │   ├── execute.go\n42: │   ├── files.go\n43: │   └── files/                   — file management subpackage\n44: ├── workloadmanager/             — workload manager business logic (existing)\n45: │   ├── reconciler/\n46: │   │   ├── reconciler.go        — SandboxReconciler (informer + workqueue)\n47: │   │   ├── types.go             — ReconcilerDeps, Store interface, constants\n48: │   │   ├── sync.go\n49: │   │   ├── pod.go\n50: │   │   ├── agentruntime.go\n51: │   │   ├── codeinterpreter.go\n52: │   │   ├── event_handlers.go\n53: │   │   └── metrics.go\n54: │   ├── handler/\n55: │   │   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go — LifecycleManager (GC, status, list, extend TTL)\n56: │   │   ├── sandbox_create.go    — SandboxCreateHandler (create AR/CI sandboxes)\n57: │   │   ├── sandbox_delete.go    — SandboxDeleteHandler\n58: │   │   ├── models.go            — Request/Response types, SandboxInfo\n59: │   │   ├── constants.go         — GVRs, labels, annotations\n60: │   │   └── sandbox_lifecycle_test.go\n61: │   └── response/\n62: │       └── response.go          — HTTP response helpers\n63: ├── router/                      — router business logic (existing)\n64: │   ├── server.go                — Server struct, route registration, Start/Run/Shutdown\n65: │   ├── config.go                — Config, NewDefaultConfig\n66: │   ├── proxy.go                 — handleInvoke, forwardToSandbox (reverse proxy)\n67: │   ├── router.go                — Router interface + implementation\n68: │   ├── backend.go               — Backend struct\n69: │   ├── loadbalancer.go          — LoadBalancer interface\n70: │   ├── informer.go              — InformerManager (watches AR/CI CRs)\n71: │   ├── middleware.go            — Auth, concurrency limit\n72: │   ├── jwt.go                   — JWTManager (RS256)\n73: │   ├── session_manager.go       — SessionManager (store-backed)\n74: │   ├── health.go                — Health check handlers\n75: │   ├── errors.go                — Error types\n76: │   └── config_test.go, server_test.go, ...\n77: ├── store/                       — shared store abstraction (Redis/Valkey)\n78: │   ├── store.go\n79: │   ├── singleton.go\n80: │   ├── codec.go\n81: │   ├── store_redis.go\n82: │   └── store_valkey.go\n83: ├── apis/\n84: │   ├── runtime/v1alpha1/        — AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types\n85: │   └── agents/v1alpha1/         — Sandbox CR types\n86: └── common/types/\n87:     └── types.go                 — shared type constants\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### 1.3 Data Flow\n91: \n92: ```\n93: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n94: │                              Kubernetes Cluster                              │\n95: │                                                                              │\n96: │  ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────┐  │\n97: │  │  agentd      │   │workloadmgr   │   │   router     │   │   picod      │  │\n98: │  │ (controller) │   │  (API srv)   │   │  (proxy)     │   │ (in-sandbox) │  │\n99: │  └──────┬───────┘   └──────┬───────┘   └──────┬───────┘   └──────┬───────┘  │\n100: │         │                  │                  │                  │           │\n101: │    watches             CRUD on            reads session      serves API     │\n102: │    Sandbox             Sandbox CRs        info from store    on PodIP       │\n103: │    CRs                 creates/deletes                        │              │\n104: │    → reconciles        sandboxes          ┌───┴───┐           │           │\n105: │    → manages Pods      │                  │ store │◄──────────┘           │\n106: │                        │                  │(Redis)│  entryPoints           │\n107: │                        ▼                  └───┬───┘                        │\n108: │              ┌─────────────────┐              │                            │\n109: │              │  LifecycleMgr   │              │ session lookup             │\n110: │              │  (GC: TTL/idle/ │              │ + JWT forward              │\n111: │              │   orphan/ghost) │              │                            │\n112: │              └─────────────────┘              ▼                            │\n113: │                                                               Client HTTP   │\n114: │                                                                    │        │\n115: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────┘\n116:                                                                      │\n117:                         Client → router (JWT auth) → proxy → picod ←─┘\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **关键交互路径：**\n121: \n122: 1. **创建沙箱**：Client → `workloadmanager` API → 创建 Sandbox CR → `agentd` 调谐 → Pod 启动 → `picod` 就绪 → `workloadmanager` 写入 store（entryPoints）\n123: 2. **请求沙箱**：Client → `router`（JWT 鉴权）→ 查 store 获取 session → 反向代理到 Pod IP:Port → `picod`\n124: 3. **清理沙箱**：`workloadmanager.LifecycleManager` 定时 GC → 删除过期/空闲 Sandbox CR → `agentd` 调谐删除 Pod\n125: \n126: ### 1.4 Dependencies\n127: \n128: | Binary | Direct Dependencies | Purpose |\n129: |--------|-------------------|---------|\n130: | `agentd` | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`, `k8s.io/api/core/v1`, `pkg/apis/agents/v1alpha1` | Controller-runtime manager, Sandbox CR scheme |\n131: | `picod` | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `k8s.io/klog/v2` | HTTP server, structured logging |\n132: | `workloadmanager` | `client-go/clientset`, `client-go/informers`, `client-go/listers`, `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic`, `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes`, `pkg/store`, `pkg/workloadmanager/*` | Typed client, informers, dynamic client, store, handlers |\n133: | `router` | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `client-go/clientset`, `client-go/informers`, `pkg/store`, `pkg/router/*` | HTTP proxy, informer-driven routing, store-backed sessions |\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## 2. Data Structures\n138: \n139: ### 2.1 `workloadmanager` — CLI Config\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: type Config struct {\n143:     Port                  string\n144:     Debug                 bool\n145:     Kubeconfig            string\n146:     Namespace             string\n147:     Workers               int\n148:     StoreType             string\n149:     StoreAddr             string\n150:     StorePassword         string\n151:     StoreDB               int\n152:     SessionCheckInterval  time.Duration\n153:     SessionIdleTimeout    time.Duration\n154:     SessionMaxDuration    time.Duration\n155:     EnableAuth            bool\n156:     MetricsPort           string\n157: }\n158: \n159: func NewDefaultConfig() *Config {\n160:     return &Config{\n161:         Port:                  \"8080\",\n162:         Debug:                 false,\n163:         Kubeconfig:            \"\",\n164:         Namespace:             \"\",\n165:         Workers:               2,\n166:         StoreType:             \"redis\",\n167:         StoreAddr:             \"localhost:6379\",\n168:         StoreDB:               0,\n169:         SessionCheckInterval:  5 * time.Minute,\n170:         SessionIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n171:         SessionMaxDuration:    24 * time.Hour,\n172:         EnableAuth:            false,\n173:         MetricsPort:           \"9090\",\n174:     }\n175: }\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ### 2.2 `router` — CLI Config\n179: \n180: ```go\n181: type Config struct {\n182:     Port                  string\n183:     Debug                 bool\n184:     EnableTLS             bool\n185:     TLSCert               string\n186:     TLSKey                string\n187:     MaxConcurrentRequests int\n188:     Kubeconfig            string\n189:     Namespace             string\n190:     SessionCheckInterval  time.Duration\n191:     SessionIdleTimeout    time.Duration\n192:     SessionMaxDuration    time.Duration\n193:     StoreType             string\n194:     StoreAddr             string\n195:     StorePassword         string\n196:     StoreDB               int\n197:     JWTExpiration         time.Duration\n198:     JWTIssuer             string\n199:     JWTLeeway             time.Duration\n200: }\n201: ```\n202: \n203: `router.Config` 已存在于 `pkg/router/config.go`，与 `NewDefaultConfig()` 对齐。\n204: \n205: ### 2.3 Shared Types (reference from existing packages)\n206: \n207: | Type | Source | Used By |\n208: |------|--------|---------|\n209: | `SandboxInfo` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager, router (via store) |\n210: | `CreateSandboxRequest` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager |\n211: | `CreateSandboxResponse` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager |\n212: | `EntryPoint` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager, router |\n213: | `ReconcilerDeps` | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go` | workloadmanager |\n214: | `Store` (interface) | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go` + `pkg/store/` | workloadmanager, router |\n215: | `Config` (router) | `pkg/router/config.go` | router |\n216: | `JWTConfig` | `pkg/router/config.go` | router |\n217: \n218: ### 2.4 Constants\n219: \n220: ```go\n221: // From pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go\n222: var (\n223:     AgentRuntimeGVR    = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\n224:     CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\n225:     SandboxGVR         = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n226:     SandboxClaimGVR    = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n227: )\n228: \n229: const (\n230:     LabelManagedBy      = \"app.kubernetes.io/managed-by\"\n231:     LabelManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n232:     LabelSessionID      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n233:     LabelWorkloadName   = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n234:     LabelSandboxName    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n235: )\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## 3. API Contracts\n241: \n242: ### 3.1 `workloadmanager` HTTP API\n243: \n244: | Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n245: |--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n246: | `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox` / `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox` | Optional (Bearer token) | Create sandbox from AR/CI template |\n247: | `DELETE` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `DeleteSandbox` | Optional | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n248: | `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `GetSandboxStatus` | Optional | Get sandbox status |\n249: | `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `ListSandboxes` | Optional | List sandboxes (?namespace=&status=) |\n250: | `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend` | `ExtendSandboxTTL` | Optional | Extend sandbox TTL |\n251: | `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` | None | Liveness probe |\n252: | `GET` | `/health/ready` | `handleHealthReady` | None | Readiness probe |\n253: \n254: **Create Sandbox Request:**\n255: ```json\n256: {\n257:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n258:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n259:   \"namespace\": \"default\"\n260: }\n261: ```\n262: \n263: **Create Sandbox Response (200):**\n264: ```json\n265: {\n266:   \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n267:   \"sandboxId\": \"k8s-uid\",\n268:   \"sandboxName\": \"my-agent-abc12345\",\n269:   \"entryPoints\": [\n270:     {\"path\": \"/\", \"protocol\": \"HTTP\", \"endpoint\": \"10.0.0.1:8080\"}\n271:   ]\n272: }\n273: ```\n274: \n275: ### 3.2 `router` HTTP API\n276: \n277: | Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n278: |--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n279: | `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` | None | Liveness probe |\n280: | `GET` | `/health/ready` | `handleHealthReady` | None | Readiness probe |\n281: | `GET/POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleAgentInvoke` | JWT (RS256) | Proxy to AgentRuntime sandbox |\n282: | `GET/POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | JWT (RS256) | Proxy to CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n283: \n284: **Proxy Flow:**\n285: 1. Extract `namespace` + `name` from URL path\n286: 2. Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header (optional — creates new session if absent)\n287: 3. Look up or create session via `SessionManager` (store-backed)\n288: 4. Resolve sandbox `entryPoints` from CR template or store\n289: 5. Select entry point by path prefix match\n290: 6. Reverse proxy request to `PodIP:Port` via `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`\n291: 7. Inject `X-Forwarded-*` headers + `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n292: 8. Update `LastActivityAt` in store\n293: \n294: ### 3.3 `agentd` — No HTTP API\n295: \n296: `agentd` is a pure controller-runtime manager. It exposes:\n297: - **Metrics**: disabled (`BindAddress: \"0\"`)\n298: - **Health probes**: disabled (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`)\n299: \n300: Communication is entirely via Kubernetes API (watch/reconcile Sandbox CRs).\n301: \n302: ### 3.4 `picod` HTTP API\n303: \n304: | Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n305: |--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n306: | `POST` | `/api/execute` | `ExecuteHandler` | JWT | Execute code in sandbox |\n307: | `POST` | `/api/files/read` | `ReadFileHandler` | JWT | Read file content (Base64) |\n308: | `POST` | `/api/files/write` | `WriteFileHandler` | JWT | Write file content (Base64) |\n309: | `GET` | `/api/files/stat` | `StatFileHandler` | JWT | File metadata |\n310: | `GET` | `/api/files` | `ListFilesHandler` | JWT | List directory |\n311: | `POST` | `/api/files/upload` | `UploadFileHandler` | JWT | Upload file (multipart/JSON) |\n312: | `GET` | `/api/files/download` | `DownloadFileHandler` | JWT | Download file (Range support) |\n313: | `POST` | `/api/files/delete` | `DeleteFileHandler` | JWT | Delete file(s) |\n314: | `POST` | `/api/files/move` | `MoveFileHandler` | JWT | Move/rename file |\n315: | `POST` | `/api/files/mkdir` | `MkDirHandler` | JWT | Create directory |\n316: | `POST` | `/api/files/search` | `SearchFilesHandler` | JWT | Search files by glob |\n317: | `POST` | `/api/files/chmod` | `ChmodHandler` | JWT | Change file permissions |\n318: | `GET` | `/health` | `HealthCheckHandler` | None | Health check |\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## 4. Core Implementation\n323: \n324: ### 4.1 `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: package main\n328: \n329: import (\n330:     \"flag\"\n331:     \"fmt\"\n332:     \"net/http\"\n333:     \"os\"\n334:     \"os/signal\"\n335:     \"syscall\"\n336:     \"time\"\n337: \n338:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n339:     \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n340:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n341:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n342:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n343:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n344: \n345:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset\"\n346:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n347:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n348:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n349:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler\"\n350:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n351: )\n352: \n353: func main() {\n354:     cfg := parseFlags()\n355: \n356:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n357:     if cfg.Debug {\n358:         flag.Set(\"v\", \"4\")\n359:     }\n360: \n361:     restConfig, err := buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)\n362:     if err != nil {\n363:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n364:     }\n365: \n366:     kubeClientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n367:     if err != nil {\n368:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create kubernetes clientset: %v\", err)\n369:     }\n370: \n371:     dynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n372:     if err != nil {\n373:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create dynamic client: %v\", err)\n374:     }\n375: \n376:     acClientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n377:     if err != nil {\n378:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %v\", err)\n379:     }\n380: \n381:     informerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n382:         ac_clientset,\n383:         30*time.Second,\n384:         externalversions.WithNamespace(cfg.Namespace),\n385:     )\n386: \n387:     arLister := informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Lister()\n388:     ciLister := informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Lister()\n389: \n390:     store.Init(&store.Config{\n391:         Type:     cfg.StoreType,\n392:         Address:  cfg.StoreAddr,\n393:         Password: cfg.StorePassword,\n394:         DB:       cfg.StoreDB,\n395:     })\n396:     storeClient := store.Storage()\n397: \n398:     reconcilerDeps := reconciler.ReconcilerDeps{\n399:         Clientset:       acClientset,\n400:         InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n401:         ARLister:        arLister,\n402:         CILister:        ciLister,\n403:         Store:           storeClient,\n404:         Workers:         cfg.Workers,\n405:     }\n406:     sandboxReconciler := reconciler.NewSandboxReconciler(reconcilerDeps)\n407: \n408:     lifecycleDeps := &handler.LifecycleManagerDeps{\n409:         DynamicClient:      dynamicClient,\n410:         Store:              storeClient,\n411:         CheckInterval:      cfg.SessionCheckInterval,\n412:         DefaultTTL:         cfg.SessionMaxDuration,\n413:         DefaultIdleTimeout: cfg.SessionIdleTimeout,\n414:     }\n415:     lifecycleManager := handler.NewLifecycleManager(lifecycleDeps)\n416: \n417:     createHandlerDeps := &handler.SandboxCreateHandlerDeps{\n418:         DynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n419:         Clientset:       acClientset,\n420:         KubeClientset:   kubeClientset,\n421:         InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n422:         Store:           storeClient,\n423:         Reconciler:      sandboxReconciler,\n424:         EnableAuth:      cfg.EnableAuth,\n425:     }\n426:     createHandler := handler.NewSandboxCreateHandler(createHandlerDeps)\n427: \n428:     deleteHandlerDeps := &handler.SandboxDeleteHandlerDeps{\n429:         DynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n430:         Store:           storeClient,\n431:         InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n432:         EnableAuth:      cfg.EnableAuth,\n433:     }\n434:     deleteHandler := handler.NewSandboxDeleteHandler(deleteHandlerDeps)\n435: \n436:     stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n437:     go sandboxReconciler.Run(stopCh)\n438: \n439:     ctx := signalHandlerContext()\n440:     go lifecycleManager.Start(ctx)\n441: \n442:     if cfg.Debug {\n443:         gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)\n444:     } else {\n445:         gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n446:     }\n447:     engine := gin.New()\n448:     engine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n449: \n450:     engine.GET(\"/health/live\", handleLive)\n451:     engine.GET(\"/health/ready\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n452:         response.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n453:     })\n454: \n455:     v1 := engine.Group(\"/api/v1\")\n456:     v1.POST(\"/sandboxes\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n457:         var req handler.CreateSandboxRequest\n458:         if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n459:             response.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, http.StatusBadRequest, \"Invalid request body\")\n460:             return\n461:         }\n462:         switch req.Kind {\n463:         case handler.AgentRuntimeKind:\n464:             createHandler.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(c)\n465:         case handler.CodeInterpreterKind:\n466:             createHandler.CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(c)\n467:         default:\n468:             response.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, http.StatusBadRequest,\n469:                 fmt.Sprintf(\"invalid kind %q\", req.Kind))\n470:         }\n471:     })\n472:     v1.DELETE(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID\", deleteHandler.DeleteSandbox)\n473:     v1.GET(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID\", lifecycleManager.GetSandboxStatus)\n474:     v1.GET(\"/sandboxes\", lifecycleManager.ListSandboxes)\n475:     v1.POST(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend\", lifecycleManager.ExtendSandboxTTL)\n476: \n477:     server := &http.Server{\n478:         Addr:    \":\" + cfg.Port,\n479:         Handler: engine,\n480:     }\n481: \n482:     go func() {\n483:         klog.Infof(\"workloadmanager listening on %s\", cfg.Port)\n484:         if err := server.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n485:             klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n486:         }\n487:     }()\n488: \n489:     <-ctx.Done()\n490:     klog.Info(\"shutting down workloadmanager...\")\n491:     close(stopCh)\n492:     lifecycleManager.Stop()\n493:     server.Shutdown(ctx)\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ### 4.2 `cmd/router/main.go`\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: package main\n501: \n502: import (\n503:     \"flag\"\n504:     \"os\"\n505:     \"os/signal\"\n506:     \"syscall\"\n507:     \"time\"\n508: \n509:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n510:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n511:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n512: \n513:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset\"\n514:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n515:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n516: )\n517: \n518: func main() {\n519:     cfg := parseFlags()\n520: \n521:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n522: \n523:     restConfig, err := buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)\n524:     if err != nil {\n525:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n526:     }\n527: \n528:     acClientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n529:     if err != nil {\n530:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %v\", err)\n531:     }\n532: \n533:     store.Init(&store.Config{\n534:         Type:     cfg.StoreType,\n535:         Address:  cfg.StoreAddr,\n536:         Password: cfg.StorePassword,\n537:         DB:       cfg.StoreDB,\n538:     })\n539: \n540:     server, err := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n541:         Port:                  cfg.Port,\n542:         Debug:                 cfg.Debug,\n543:         EnableTLS:             cfg.EnableTLS,\n544:         TLSCert:               cfg.TLSCert,\n545:         TLSKey:                cfg.TLSKey,\n546:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n547:         SessionCheckInterval:  cfg.SessionCheckInterval,\n548:         SessionIdleTimeout:    cfg.SessionIdleTimeout,\n549:         SessionMaxDuration:    cfg.SessionMaxDuration,\n550:         StoreType:             cfg.StoreType,\n551:         JWTExpiration:         cfg.JWTExpiration,\n552:         JWTIssuer:             cfg.JWTIssuer,\n553:         JWTLeeway:             cfg.JWTLeeway,\n554:     })\n555:     if err != nil {\n556:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create router server: %v\", err)\n557:     }\n558: \n559:     informerManager := router.NewInformerManager(acClientset, server.GetRouter())\n560:     stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n561:     go informerManager.Start(stopCh)\n562: \n563:     go server.Run()\n564: \n565:     sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n566:     signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n567:     <-sigCh\n568: \n569:     klog.Info(\"shutting down router...\")\n570:     close(stopCh)\n571: }\n572: ```\n573: \n574: ### 4.3 Flag Parsing\n575: \n576: **`workloadmanager` flags:**\n577: \n578: | Flag | Env | Default | Description |\n579: |------|-----|---------|-------------|\n580: | `--port` | `WM_PORT` | `8080` | HTTP listen port |\n581: | `--debug` | `WM_DEBUG` | `false` | Debug mode (verbose logging) |\n582: | `--kubeconfig` | `KUBECONFIG` | in-cluster | Path to kubeconfig |\n583: | `--namespace` | `WM_NAMESPACE` | `\"\"` (all) | Watch namespace scope |\n584: | `--workers` | `WM_WORKERS` | `2` | Reconciler worker count |\n585: | `--store-type` | `WM_STORE_TYPE` | `redis` | Store backend (`redis`/`valkey`) |\n586: | `--store-addr` | `WM_STORE_ADDR` | `localhost:6379` | Store address |\n587: | `--store-password` | `WM_STORE_PASSWORD` | `\"\"` | Store password |\n588: | `--store-db` | `WM_STORE_DB` | `0` | Store DB index |\n589: | `--session-check-interval` | `WM_SESSION_CHECK_INTERVAL` | `5m` | GC check interval |\n590: | `--session-idle-timeout` | `WM_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | `30m` | Idle timeout |\n591: | `--session-max-duration` | `WM_SESSION_MAX_DURATION` | `24h` | Max session TTL |\n592: | `--enable-auth` | `WM_ENABLE_AUTH` | `false` | Enable Bearer token auth |\n593: \n594: **`router` flags:**\n595: \n596: | Flag | Env | Default | Description |\n597: |------|-----|---------|-------------|\n598: | `--port` | `ROUTER_PORT` | `8080` | HTTP listen port |\n599: | `--debug` | `ROUTER_DEBUG` | `false` | Debug mode |\n600: | `--enable-tls` | `ROUTER_ENABLE_TLS` | `false` | Enable HTTPS |\n601: | `--tls-cert` | `ROUTER_TLS_CERT` | `\"\"` | TLS certificate path |\n602: | `--tls-key` | `ROUTER_TLS_KEY` | `\"\"` | TLS key path |\n603: | `--max-concurrent-requests` | `ROUTER_MAX_CONCURRENT` | `1000` | Concurrency limit |\n604: | `--kubeconfig` | `KUBECONFIG` | in-cluster | Path to kubeconfig |\n605: | `--namespace` | `ROUTER_NAMESPACE` | `\"\"` (all) | Watch namespace scope |\n606: | `--store-type` | `ROUTER_STORE_TYPE` | `redis` | Store backend |\n607: | `--store-addr` | `ROUTER_STORE_ADDR` | `localhost:6379` | Store address |\n608: | `--store-password` | `ROUTER_STORE_PASSWORD` | `\"\"` | Store password |\n609: | `--store-db` | `ROUTER_STORE_DB` | `0` | Store DB index |\n610: | `--jwt-expiration` | `ROUTER_JWT_EXPIRATION` | `5m` | JWT token TTL |\n611: | `--jwt-issuer` | `ROUTER_JWT_ISSUER` | `agentcube-router` | JWT issuer claim |\n612: | `--jwt-leeway` | `ROUTER_JWT_LEEWAY` | `1m` | JWT clock skew leeway |\n613: \n614: ### 4.4 Kubeconfig Resolution\n615: \n616: Both `workloadmanager` and `router` use the same resolution strategy:\n617: \n618: ```go\n619: func buildKubeConfig(kubeconfig string) (*rest.Config, error) {\n620:     if kubeconfig != \"\" {\n621:         return clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n622:     }\n623:     if cfg, err := rest.InClusterConfig(); err == nil {\n624:         return cfg, nil\n625:     }\n626:     return clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", clientcmd.RecommendedHomeFile)\n627: }\n628: ```\n629: \n630: Priority: explicit flag → in-cluster config → `~/.kube/config`.\n631: \n632: ### 4.5 Store Initialization\n633: \n634: Store is a singleton initialized at startup via `pkg/store`:\n635: \n636: ```go\n637: // pkg/store/singleton.go\n638: var (\n639:     singleton Store\n640:     once      sync.Once\n641: )\n642: \n643: func Init(cfg *Config) {\n644:     once.Do(func() {\n645:         switch cfg.Type {\n646:         case \"valkey\":\n647:             singleton = NewValkeyStore(cfg)\n648:         default:\n649:             singleton = NewRedisStore(cfg)\n650:         }\n651:     })\n652: }\n653: \n654: func Storage() Store {\n655:     return singleton\n656: }\n657: ```\n658: \n659: ---\n660: \n661: ## 5. Error Handling\n662: \n663: ### 5.1 Error Categories\n664: \n665: | Category | Binary | Strategy |\n666: |----------|--------|----------|\n667: | Startup failure | All | `klog.Fatalf` + `os.Exit(1)` — non-recoverable |\n668: | Kubeconfig failure | workloadmanager, router | Fatal exit — cannot function without K8s access |\n669: | Store connection failure | workloadmanager, router | Fatal exit on init; retry on runtime (store client handles reconnect) |\n670: | Informer cache sync timeout | workloadmanager, router | Log error, continue — degraded mode (stale data) |\n671: | Reconciler error | workloadmanager | Requeue with exponential backoff (5s → 5min, max 15 retries) |\n672: | Sandbox creation timeout | workloadmanager | Rollback CR deletion, return 500 to client |\n673: | Proxy backend unreachable | router | Return 502 `{\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}` |\n674: | Proxy timeout | router | Return 504 `{\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}` |\n675: | JWT validation failure | router | Return 401 — request rejected |\n676: | GC cleanup failure | workloadmanager | Log error, continue to next entry — no abort |\n677: \n678: ### 5.2 Graceful Shutdown\n679: \n680: | Binary | Shutdown Sequence |\n681: |--------|------------------|\n682: | `agentd` | `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()` → manager.Stop() → reconciler finalizers |\n683: | `picod` | `SIGINT/SIGTERM` → `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with 10s timeout |\n684: | `workloadmanager` | Signal → `close(stopCh)` (reconciler) → `lifecycleManager.Stop()` → HTTP server graceful shutdown |\n685: | `router` | Signal → `close(stopCh)` (informers) → `server.Shutdown(ctx)` |\n686: \n687: ### 5.3 Sentinel Errors\n688: \n689: ```go\n690: // router/session_manager.go\n691: type SessionNotFoundError struct { SessionID string }\n692: type SandboxTemplateNotFoundError struct { Namespace, Name, Kind string }\n693: \n694: // workloadmanager handler\n695: var (\n696:     ErrPathTraversal     = errors.New(\"access denied: workspace jail violation\")\n697:     ErrFileNotFound      = errors.New(\"file not found\")\n698:     // ... (from picod/files/)\n699: )\n700: ```\n701: \n702: ---\n703: \n704: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n705: \n706: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n707: \n708: #### `cmd/workloadmanager/main_test.go`\n709: \n710: | Test Name | Description |\n711: |-----------|-------------|\n712: | `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags → default config values |\n713: | `TestParseFlags_CustomValues` | All flags set → reflected in config |\n714: | `TestParseFlags_EnvOverrides` | Environment variables override defaults |\n715: | `TestBuildKubeConfig_InCluster` | In-cluster config when no flag + in-cluster env |\n716: | `TestBuildKubeConfig_ExplicitPath` | Explicit kubeconfig path takes priority |\n717: \n718: #### `cmd/router/main_test.go`\n719: \n720: | Test Name | Description |\n721: |-----------|-------------|\n722: | `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags → default config values |\n723: | `TestParseFlags_CustomValues` | All flags set → reflected in config |\n724: | `TestParseFlags_TLSConfig` | `--enable-tls --tls-cert --tls-key` → TLS config populated |\n725: | `TestParseFlags_JWTConfig` | JWT flags → correct durations and issuer |\n726: \n727: ### 6.2 Integration Test Strategy\n728: \n729: - **E2E sandbox lifecycle**: Use `envtest` (controller-runtime) to spin up a local API server, create AR/CI CRs, verify reconciler behavior\n730: - **Store mocking**: Use `miniredis` (already in `go.mod` as `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2`) for Redis-backed tests\n731: - **Proxy tests**: Use `httptest.NewServer` as fake picod backend, verify router forwards correctly with JWT\n732: - **Flag parsing isolation**: Test `parseFlags()` with isolated `flag.FlagSet` to avoid global state pollution\n733: \n734: ### 6.3 Gate Requirements\n735: \n736: 1. `go build ./cmd/...` compiles all 4 binaries\n737: 2. `go vet ./cmd/...` produces no warnings\n738: 3. `go test ./cmd/... -v` all pass\n739: 4. `go test -race ./cmd/...` no data race warnings\n740: 5. `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n741: 6. Each binary's `main.go` ≤ 100 lines (logic delegated to `pkg/`)\n742: 7. Flag parsing tests cover defaults, custom values, and env overrides\n743: \n744: ---\n745: \n746: ## 7. Deployment Considerations\n747: \n748: ### 7.1 Container Images\n749: \n750: | Binary | Image | Run As | Port |\n751: |--------|-------|--------|------|\n752: | `agentd` | `agentcube-agentd` | Non-root (65534) | None (controller) |\n753: | `picod` | Built into sandbox image | User-defined | 8080 (configurable) |\n754: | `workloadmanager` | `agentcube-workloadmanager` | Non-root (65534) | 8080 |\n755: | `router` | `agentcube-router` | Non-root (65534) | 8080 |\n756: \n757: ### 7.2 RBAC Requirements\n758: \n759: | Binary | Resources | Verbs |\n760: |--------|-----------|-------|\n761: | `agentd` | `sandboxes`, `sandboxclaims`, `pods`, `events` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n762: | `workloadmanager` | `agentruntimes`, `codeinterpreters`, `sandboxes`, `sandboxclaims`, `pods`, `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `delete` |\n763: | `router` | `agentruntimes`, `codeinterpreters`, `secrets` (read public key) | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n764: \n765: ### 7.3 Resource Limits\n766: \n767: | Binary | CPU Request | Memory Request | CPU Limit | Memory Limit |\n768: |--------|------------|----------------|-----------|--------------|\n769: | `agentd` | 100m | 128Mi | 500m | 512Mi |\n770: | `workloadmanager` | 100m | 128Mi | 500m | 512Mi |\n771: | `router` | 200m | 256Mi | 1000m | 1Gi |\n772: \n773: ### 7.4 Store Dependency\n774: \n775: Both `workloadmanager` and `router` require a Redis/Valkey instance. The store connection is established at startup; failure is fatal. For production:\n776: - Use Redis Sentinel or Valkey Cluster for HA\n777: - Configure `--store-password` via Kubernetes Secret\n778: - Set appropriate `--store-db` to isolate environments\n779: \n780: ### 7.5 Metrics\n781: \n782: - `workloadmanager`: Reconciler metrics (total, duration, errors, workqueue depth), GC metrics (cleanup total, duration, errors)\n783: - `router`: Request latency, proxy errors, JWT validation failures, concurrent request count\n784: - Metrics exposed on separate port (`--metrics-port`, default `9090`) via Prometheus `/metrics` endpoint\n785: \n786: ---\n787: \n788: ## 8. Implementation Steps\n789: \n790: ### Phase 1: `workloadmanager` CLI Entry (Day 1)\n791: \n792: 1. Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n793: 2. Implement `parseFlags()` with env fallback\n794: 3. Implement `buildKubeConfig()` helper\n795: 4. Wire up: kube clients → informer factory → store → reconciler → lifecycle manager → HTTP server\n796: 5. Add graceful shutdown (signal → stopCh → lifecycle stop → server shutdown)\n797: 6. Write `main_test.go` (flag parsing, kubeconfig resolution)\n798: \n799: ### Phase 2: `router` CLI Entry (Day 2)\n800: \n801: 1. Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n802: 2. Implement `parseFlags()` with env fallback\n803: 3. Wire up: kube client → store → `router.NewServer()` → `InformerManager` → `server.Run()`\n804: 4. Add graceful shutdown (signal → informer stop → server shutdown)\n805: 5. Write `main_test.go` (flag parsing, TLS config, JWT config)\n806: \n807: ### Phase 3: Build & Verification (Day 3)\n808: \n809: 1. `go build ./cmd/...` — all 4 binaries compile\n810: 2. `go vet ./cmd/...` — no warnings\n811: 3. `go test ./cmd/... -v` — all tests pass\n812: 4. `go test -race ./cmd/...` — no races\n813: 5. `go mod tidy` — no changes\n814: 6. Verify binary sizes and startup times\n815: \n816: ### Phase 4: Dockerfile & Deployment (Day 4)\n817: \n818: 1. Create multi-stage Dockerfiles for `workloadmanager` and `router`\n819: 2. Add Helm chart templates for new deployments\n820: 3. Document RBAC, resource limits, and env vars\n821: \n822: ---\n823: \n824: ## 9. Future Changes\n825: \n826: | Change | Description | Priority |\n827: |--------|-------------|----------|\n828: | AR-0XX | Unified `agentcube` CLI binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.) | P2 |\n829: | AR-0XX | Prometheus metrics endpoint for all binaries | P1 |\n830: | AR-0XX | Structured logging (zap/slog) across all binaries | P2 |\n831: | AR-0XX | Health probe endpoints for `agentd` (currently disabled) | P2 |\n832: | AR-0XX | `workloadmanager` warm pool management API for CodeInterpreters | P1 |\n833: | AR-0XX | Router dynamic route registration from informer events (currently placeholder) | P1 |\n834: \n835: ### Known Limitations\n836: \n837: - `router.InformerManager` event handlers are stubs (`klog.V(4).Infof`) — dynamic route registration not yet implemented\n838: - `agentd` has metrics and health probes disabled — observability gap\n839: - No mutual TLS between `router` and `picod` — JWT provides auth but not transport security\n840: - `workloadmanager` and `router` share the same store instance — no isolation if one corrupts data\n841: - Flag parsing uses global `flag` package — not testable in isolation without `flag.NewFlagSet`\n\n(End of file - total 841 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nAgentCube 由 4 个独立的 Go 二进制组成，各自承担明确的运行时职责：\n\n| Binary | Package | Role | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|------|---------|\n| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Sandbox CR 控制器，监听 Sandbox 资源变化并调谐 Pod 生命周期 | controller-runtime reconciler |\n| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | 沙箱内守护进程，提供代码执行 + 文件管理 API | standalone HTTP server (gin) |\n| `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | 沙箱编排 API 服务：创建/删除/列表/状态/TTL 续期 + GC 清理 | HTTP API + informer-based reconciler |\n| `router` | `cmd/router` | 反向代理网关：JWT 鉴权 → session 查找 → 请求转发到沙箱 Pod | HTTP reverse proxy + informer-driven routing |\n\n四者通过 Kubernetes API（CRD + informers）和共享 store（Redis/Valkey）协同，无直接进程间通信。\n\n### 1.2 Package Layout\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/design.md","time":{"start":1775849594772,"end":1775849594790}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849596141,"sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","part":{"id":"prt_d78e2601a001iKmWGn7WTjIQpq","messageID":"msg_d78e24cef0018H39ki6ye8nBZ4","sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_906e38cebbce4946bbc91b57","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: `agentd` binary — existing entry point\n13: \n14: The `cmd/agentd/main.go` binary SHALL remain as the Sandbox controller using controller-runtime. The binary SHALL accept `--kubeconfig` and `--master` flags for out-of-cluster Kubernetes connectivity.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: agentd starts with in-cluster config\n17: \n18: - **GIVEN** the binary runs inside a Kubernetes pod with a valid service account\n19: - **WHEN** `agentd` is invoked without `--kubeconfig` or `--master`\n20: - **THEN** it uses `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to obtain in-cluster config and starts the manager\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: agentd starts with out-of-cluster config\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file exists at `/path/to/kubeconfig`\n25: - **WHEN** `agentd --kubeconfig=/path/to/kubeconfig` is invoked\n26: - **THEN** it loads the kubeconfig and starts the manager\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: agentd graceful shutdown\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the `agentd` binary is running\n31: - **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n32: - **THEN** `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())` returns and the process exits with code 0\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: agentd fails on invalid config\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** `--kubeconfig` points to a non-existent file\n37: - **WHEN** `agentd` is invoked\n38: - **THEN** it logs the error to `setupLog` and exits with code 1\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: `picod` binary — existing entry point\n43: \n44: The `cmd/picod/main.go` binary SHALL remain as the Pico code-interpreter server. The binary SHALL use `picod.ParseFlags()` for configuration and `server.Run()` for execution with signal handling.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: picod starts with default config\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** no flags are provided\n49: - **WHEN** `picod` is invoked\n50: - **THEN** `ParseFlags()` returns a config with defaults and `server.Run()` starts the HTTP server\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: picod graceful shutdown\n53: \n54: - **GIVEN** the `picod` binary is running (via `server.Run()`)\n55: - **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n56: - **THEN** the HTTP server shuts down gracefully and the process exits with code 0\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: picod fails on port conflict\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** the configured port is already bound by another process\n61: - **WHEN** `picod` is invoked\n62: - **THEN** `server.Run()` logs the error via `klog.Fatalf` and the process exits with code 1\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: `workloadmanager` binary — new entry point\n67: \n68: A new binary SHALL be created at `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`. The binary SHALL initialize the `SandboxReconciler` from `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler` and run it with the provided configuration.\n69: \n70: The binary SHALL:\n71: \n72: 1. Parse CLI flags: `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--workers`, `--resync-period`, `--store-type`\n73: 2. Build a `rest.Config` for Kubernetes connectivity\n74: 3. Create a `clientset.Interface` from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset`\n75: 4. Create a `SharedInformerFactory` with the configured resync period\n76: 5. Create listers for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter`\n77: 6. Optionally create a Pod informer (if `--watch-pods` is true)\n78: 7. Initialize the store client via `pkg/store`\n79: 8. Construct `ReconcilerDeps` and create `SandboxReconciler`\n80: 9. Call `reconciler.Run(stopCh)` with signal handler\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: workloadmanager starts with in-cluster config\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** the binary runs inside a Kubernetes pod\n85: - **WHEN** `workloadmanager` is invoked without `--kubeconfig`\n86: - **THEN** it uses `rest.InClusterConfig()` and creates a clientset\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: workloadmanager starts with out-of-cluster config\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file exists\n91: - **WHEN** `workloadmanager --kubeconfig=/path/to/kubeconfig --master=https://api.example.com` is invoked\n92: - **THEN** it builds a `rest.Config` from the flags and creates a clientset\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: workloadmanager initializes informers\n95: \n96: - **GIVEN** a valid clientset is created\n97: - **WHEN** the binary constructs the `SharedInformerFactory`\n98: - **THEN** the factory is created with the `--resync-period` duration (default: 30s)\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: workloadmanager constructs reconciler\n101: \n102: - **GIVEN** all dependencies are initialized (clientset, informer factory, listers, store)\n103: - **WHEN** `NewSandboxReconciler(deps)` is called\n104: - **THEN** the reconciler is created with the specified `--workers` count (default: 2)\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: workloadmanager runs reconciler\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** the reconciler is constructed\n109: - **WHEN** `reconciler.Run(stopCh)` is called\n110: - **THEN** the informer factory starts, cache syncs, and worker goroutines begin processing\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: workloadmanager graceful shutdown\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is running\n115: - **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n116: - **THEN** `reconciler.Run` closes `stopCh`, the factory shuts down, the workqueue drains, and the process exits with code 0\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: workloadmanager cache sync timeout\n119: \n120: - **GIVEN** the API server is unreachable\n121: - **WHEN** `reconciler.Run` waits for cache sync\n122: - **THEN** after `cacheSyncTimeout` (30s) the reconciler logs the failure and exits with code 1\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: workloadmanager missing store\n125: \n126: - **GIVEN** `--store-type` is not set and no default store is available\n127: - **WHEN** the binary attempts to initialize the store\n128: - **THEN** it panics with \"Store is required\" (as enforced by `NewSandboxReconciler`)\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: workloadmanager help output\n131: \n132: - **GIVEN** the binary is compiled\n133: - **WHEN** `workloadmanager --help` is invoked\n134: - **THEN** the output includes `--kubeconfig`, `--master`, `--workers`, `--resync-period`, `--store-type`, and `--watch-pods` flags\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: `router` binary — new entry point\n139: \n140: A new binary SHALL be created at `cmd/router/main.go`. The binary SHALL initialize the `Server` from `pkg/router` and run it with the provided configuration.\n141: \n142: The binary SHALL:\n143: \n144: 1. Parse CLI flags: `--port`, `--debug`, `--enable-tls`, `--tls-cert`, `--tls-key`, `--max-concurrent`, `--session-check-interval`, `--session-idle-timeout`, `--session-max-duration`, `--store-type`, `--jwt-expiration`, `--jwt-issuer`, `--jwt-leeway`, `--kubeconfig`, `--master`\n145: 2. Build a `*router.Config` from flags\n146: 3. Call `router.NewServer(config)` to construct the server\n147: 4. Call `server.Run()` which handles signal-based graceful shutdown internally\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: router starts with default config\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** no flags are provided\n152: - **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n153: - **THEN** `NewDefaultConfig()` values are used and the server starts on port 8080\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: router starts with custom port\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `--port=9090` is provided\n158: - **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n159: - **THEN** the server listens on `:9090`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: router starts with TLS enabled\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `--enable-tls --tls-cert=/path/cert.pem --tls-key=/path/key.pem` are provided\n164: - **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n165: - **THEN** the server starts HTTPS using `ListenAndServeTLS`\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: router TLS enabled but missing cert/key\n168: \n169: - **GIVEN** `--enable-tls` is provided but `--tls-cert` or `--tls-key` is empty\n170: - **WHEN** `router` is invoked\n171: - **THEN** `server.Start()` returns nil (no-op) and the process exits without starting a server\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: router graceful shutdown\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** the `router` binary is running (via `server.Run()`)\n176: - **WHEN** a SIGTERM signal is received\n177: - **THEN** `server.Shutdown(ctx)` is called with a 10s timeout and the process exits with code 0\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: router JWT key initialization\n180: \n181: - **GIVEN** the server is constructed\n182: - **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` runs\n183: - **THEN** `jwtManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` is called to initialize or load the JWT signing key\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: router fails on JWT initialization error\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** the store is unreachable during JWT key loading\n188: - **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n189: - **THEN** it returns an error and the binary exits with code 1\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: router fails on session manager error\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** the store client cannot create a session manager\n194: - **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n195: - **THEN** it returns an error and the binary exits with code 1\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: router help output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** the binary is compiled\n200: - **WHEN** `router --help` is invoked\n201: - **THEN** the output includes `--port`, `--debug`, `--enable-tls`, `--tls-cert`, `--tls-key`, `--max-concurrent`, `--store-type`, and JWT-related flags\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ### Requirement: Build targets\n206: \n207: All 4 binaries SHALL be buildable from the module root.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: build agentd\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** the module root contains valid `go.mod`\n212: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd` is run\n213: - **THEN** the `agentd` binary is produced with exit code 0\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: build picod\n216: \n217: - **GIVEN** the module root contains valid `go.mod`\n218: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/picod` is run\n219: - **THEN** the `picod` binary is produced with exit code 0\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: build workloadmanager\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` exists with valid Go code\n224: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager` is run\n225: - **THEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is produced with exit code 0\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: build router\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go` exists with valid Go code\n230: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/router` is run\n231: - **THEN** the `router` binary is produced with exit code 0\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: build all binaries\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** all 4 cmd packages compile\n236: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/...` is run\n237: - **THEN** all 4 binaries are built without errors\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ### Requirement: Code quality gates\n242: \n243: The codebase SHALL pass the following checks after AR-019 implementation:\n244: \n245: - `go vet ./cmd/...` produces no warnings\n246: - `go build ./cmd/...` succeeds\n247: - `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: go vet clean\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n252: - **WHEN** `go vet ./cmd/...` is run\n253: - **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: all binaries build\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n258: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/...` is run\n259: - **THEN** exit code is 0\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: no unused dependencies\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** AR-019 is implemented\n264: - **WHEN** `go mod tidy` is run\n265: - **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` are unchanged\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## File changes\n270: \n271: | File | Action | Description |\n272: |------|--------|-------------|\n273: | `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for workload manager reconciler |\n274: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Create | CLI entry point for router/gateway server |\n275: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | No change | Existing entry point (already functional) |\n276: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | No change | Existing entry point (already functional) |\n\n(End of file - total 276 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `agentd` binary — existing entry point\n\nThe `cmd/agentd/main.go` binary SHALL remain as the Sandbox controller using controller-runtime. The binary SHALL accept `--kubeconfig` and `--master` flags for out-of-cluster Kubernetes connectivity.\n\n#### Scenario: agentd starts with in-cluster config\n\n- **GIVEN** the binary runs inside a Kubernetes pod with a valid service account\n- **WHEN** `agentd` is invoked without `--kubeconfig` or `--master`\n- **THEN** it uses `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to obtain in-cluster config and starts the manager","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849596131,"end":1775849596139}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849597438,"sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","part":{"id":"prt_d78e26576001D9R54k2iK1teHt","messageID":"msg_d78e24cef0018H39ki6ye8nBZ4","sessionID":"ses_2871dc766ffeqjjCiSYJz6qE7Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9b96b0e388554ce9a5a6138c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd\n4: > **Language:** Go\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-019/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-019/design.md`, `changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md`\n8: \n9: ## T1. 确认现有二进制 — cmd/agentd 和 cmd/picod 无变更\n10: \n11: - [ ] 1.1 审查 `cmd/agentd/main.go`（59 行）确认已满足 delta-spec 中 agentd 的全部场景\n12: - [ ] 1.2 审查 `cmd/picod/main.go`（15 行）确认已满足 delta-spec 中 picod 的全部场景\n13: - [ ] 1.3 运行 `go build ./cmd/agentd ./cmd/picod` 确认两个现有二进制编译通过\n14: - [ ] 1.4 记录 agentd 的 flag（`--kubeconfig`, `--master`）和 picod 的 flag（通过 `picod.ParseFlags()`）\n15: \n16: **Verification:** `go build ./cmd/agentd ./cmd/picod` exit 0；两个 main.go 文件无内容变更\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## T2. 实现 workloadmanager CLI 配置解析 — cmd/workloadmanager/config.go\n21: \n22: - [ ] 2.1 创建 `cmd/workloadmanager/` 目录\n23: - [ ] 2.2 创建 `cmd/workloadmanager/config.go`\n24: - [ ] 2.3 定义 `Config` 结构体，字段与 design.md §2.1 一致：\n25:   `Port`, `Debug`, `Kubeconfig`, `Namespace`, `Workers`, `StoreType`, `StoreAddr`, `StorePassword`, `StoreDB`, `SessionCheckInterval`, `SessionIdleTimeout`, `SessionMaxDuration`, `EnableAuth`, `MetricsPort`\n26: - [ ] 2.4 实现 `NewDefaultConfig() *Config` 函数，默认值与 design.md §2.1 完全对齐\n27: - [ ] 2.5 实现 `parseFlags() *Config` 函数：\n28:   - 使用 `flag.NewFlagSet` 创建独立 FlagSet（避免全局状态污染，支持测试）\n29:   - 定义全部 14 个 flag（与 design.md §4.3 workloadmanager flags 表一致）\n30:   - 每个 flag 支持环境变量回退（`envOr` 辅助函数）\n31:   - 解析 duration 类型 flag（`--session-check-interval`, `--session-idle-timeout`, `--session-max-duration`）\n32:   - 返回填充后的 `*Config`\n33: - [ ] 2.6 实现 `envOr(key, defaultVal string) string` 辅助函数\n34: - [ ] 2.7 实现 `buildKubeConfig(kubeconfig string) (*rest.Config, error)` 函数，逻辑与 design.md §4.4 一致：\n35:   - 优先级：显式 flag → `rest.InClusterConfig()` → `~/.kube/config`\n36: - [ ] 2.8 运行 `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager/...` 确认编译通过\n37: \n38: **Verification:** `config.go` 编译通过；`parseFlags()` 使用独立 FlagSet；14 个 flag 与 design.md §4.3 表一致；`buildKubeConfig` 三级回退策略正确\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## T3. 实现 workloadmanager 主入口 — cmd/workloadmanager/main.go\n43: \n44: - [ ] 3.1 创建 `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n45: - [ ] 3.2 导入依赖（与 design.md §4.1 一致）：\n46:   `flag`, `fmt`, `net/http`, `os`, `os/signal`, `syscall`, `time`,\n47:   `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`,\n48:   `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic`, `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes`, `k8s.io/client-go/rest`, `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`,\n49:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset`,\n50:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions`,\n51:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`,\n52:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler`,\n53:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler`,\n54:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response`\n55: - [ ] 3.3 `main()` 函数实现完整启动流程（与 design.md §4.1 代码样本对齐）：\n56:   - `cfg := parseFlags()`\n57:   - `klog.InitFlags(nil)`，debug 模式设置 `--v=4`\n58:   - `buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)` → `restConfig`\n59:   - 创建 `kubernetes.Clientset`, `dynamic.Client`, `agentcube.Clientset`\n60:   - 创建 `SharedInformerFactory`（30s resync，namespace 限定）\n61:   - 获取 `arLister` 和 `ciLister`\n62:   - `store.Init()` + `store.Storage()` 初始化 store 单例\n63:   - 构造 `ReconcilerDeps` → `NewSandboxReconciler()`\n64:   - 构造 `LifecycleManagerDeps` → `NewLifecycleManager()`\n65:   - 构造 `SandboxCreateHandlerDeps` → `NewSandboxCreateHandler()`\n66:   - 构造 `SandboxDeleteHandlerDeps` → `NewSandboxDeleteHandler()`\n67: - [ ] 3.4 启动 goroutine：`sandboxReconciler.Run(stopCh)`, `lifecycleManager.Start(ctx)`\n68: - [ ] 3.5 配置 gin 引擎（debug/release mode），注册路由（与 design.md §3.1 API 表一致）：\n69:   - `GET /health/live` → `handleLive`\n70:   - `GET /health/ready` → `response.JSON(200, {\"status\": \"ok\"})`\n71:   - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes` → 根据 `req.Kind` 分发到 `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox` / `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox`\n72:   - `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` → `deleteHandler.DeleteSandbox`\n73:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` → `lifecycleManager.GetSandboxStatus`\n74:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes` → `lifecycleManager.ListSandboxes`\n75:   - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend` → `lifecycleManager.ExtendSandboxTTL`\n76: - [ ] 3.6 启动 HTTP server（goroutine），监听 `cfg.Port`\n77: - [ ] 3.7 实现优雅关闭：`signalHandlerContext()` → `<-ctx.Done()` → `close(stopCh)` → `lifecycleManager.Stop()` → `server.Shutdown(ctx)`\n78: - [ ] 3.8 实现 `handleLive(c *gin.Context)` 辅助函数：返回 `response.JSON(200, {\"status\": \"ok\"})`\n79: - [ ] 3.9 实现 `signalHandlerContext() context.Context` 辅助函数：监听 `SIGINT`/`SIGTERM` 返回可取消 context\n80: - [ ] 3.10 运行 `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager/...` 确认编译通过\n81: \n82: **Verification:** `main.go` 编译通过；路由注册覆盖 design.md §3.1 全部 7 个端点；启动流程覆盖 design.md §4.1 全部依赖注入；优雅关闭覆盖 design.md §5.2 workloadmanager 序列\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## T4. 实现 router CLI 配置解析 — cmd/router/config.go\n87: \n88: - [ ] 4.1 创建 `cmd/router/` 目录\n89: - [ ] 4.2 创建 `cmd/router/config.go`\n90: - [ ] 4.3 定义 `Config` 结构体，字段与 design.md §2.2 一致：\n91:   `Port`, `Debug`, `EnableTLS`, `TLSCert`, `TLSKey`, `MaxConcurrentRequests`, `Kubeconfig`, `Namespace`, `SessionCheckInterval`, `SessionIdleTimeout`, `SessionMaxDuration`, `StoreType`, `StoreAddr`, `StorePassword`, `StoreDB`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTLeeway`\n92: - [ ] 4.4 实现 `NewDefaultConfig() *Config` 函数，默认值与 design.md §2.2 及 `pkg/router/config.go` 中的 `NewDefaultConfig()` 对齐\n93: - [ ] 4.5 实现 `parseFlags() *Config` 函数：\n94:   - 使用 `flag.NewFlagSet` 创建独立 FlagSet\n95:   - 定义全部 18 个 flag（与 design.md §4.3 router flags 表一致）\n96:   - 每个 flag 支持环境变量回退\n97:   - 解析 duration 类型 flag\n98:   - 返回填充后的 `*Config`\n99: - [ ] 4.6 复用 `envOr` 和 `buildKubeConfig` 辅助函数（与 T2 相同的模式）\n100: - [ ] 4.7 运行 `go build ./cmd/router/...` 确认编译通过\n101: \n102: **Verification:** `config.go` 编译通过；`parseFlags()` 使用独立 FlagSet；18 个 flag 与 design.md §4.3 表一致；默认值与 `pkg/router/config.go` 对齐\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## T5. 实现 router 主入口 — cmd/router/main.go\n107: \n108: - [ ] 5.1 创建 `cmd/router/main.go`\n109: - [ ] 5.2 导入依赖（与 design.md §4.2 一致）：\n110:   `flag`, `os`, `os/signal`, `syscall`, `time`,\n111:   `k8s.io/client-go/rest`, `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`,\n112:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset`,\n113:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`,\n114:   `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n115: - [ ] 5.3 `main()` 函数实现完整启动流程（与 design.md §4.2 代码样本对齐）：\n116:   - `cfg := parseFlags()`\n117:   - `klog.InitFlags(nil)`\n118:   - `buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)` → `restConfig`\n119:   - 创建 `agentcube.Clientset`\n120:   - `store.Init()` 初始化 store 单例\n121:   - 构造 `*router.Config` → `router.NewServer(config)`\n122:   - 创建 `router.NewInformerManager(acClientset, server.GetRouter())`\n123:   - 启动 goroutine：`informerManager.Start(stopCh)`, `server.Run()`\n124: - [ ] 5.4 实现优雅关闭：`signal.Notify(sigCh, SIGINT, SIGTERM)` → `<-sigCh` → `close(stopCh)` → `server.Shutdown(ctx)`（10s timeout）\n125: - [ ] 5.5 运行 `go build ./cmd/router/...` 确认编译通过\n126: \n127: **Verification:** `main.go` 编译通过；启动流程覆盖 design.md §4.2 全部步骤；优雅关闭覆盖 design.md §5.2 router 序列；InformerManager 和 Server 正确启动\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## T6. 单元测试 — workloadmanager flag 解析和 kubeconfig\n132: \n133: - [ ] 6.1 创建 `cmd/workloadmanager/config_test.go`\n134: - [ ] 6.2 测试 `TestParseFlags_Defaults`：无 flag → 所有字段为 `NewDefaultConfig()` 默认值\n135: - [ ] 6.3 测试 `TestParseFlags_CustomValues`：设置全部 14 个 flag → Config 字段完全匹配\n136: - [ ] 6.4 测试 `TestParseFlags_EnvOverrides`：设置环境变量（`WM_PORT`, `WM_DEBUG`, `WM_STORE_TYPE` 等）→ 覆盖默认值\n137: - [ ] 6.5 测试 `TestParseFlags_EnvAndFlagPrecedence`：flag 和环境变量同时设置 → flag 优先\n138: - [ ] 6.6 测试 `TestBuildKubeConfig_ExplicitPath`：传入有效 kubeconfig 路径 → 返回非 nil `*rest.Config`\n139: - [ ] 6.7 测试 `TestParseFlags_HelpOutput`：`--help` 输出包含全部 14 个 flag 名称（覆盖 delta-spec workloadmanager help output 场景）\n140: - [ ] 6.8 测试 `TestParseFlags_DurationParsing`：`--session-check-interval=10m` → `10 * time.Minute`\n141: \n142: **Verification:** `go test ./cmd/workloadmanager/... -v -count=1` 全部通过；覆盖 delta-spec §Requirement: workloadmanager help output 场景\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## T7. 单元测试 — router flag 解析和配置\n147: \n148: - [ ] 7.1 创建 `cmd/router/config_test.go`\n149: - [ ] 7.2 测试 `TestParseFlags_Defaults`：无 flag → 所有字段为 `NewDefaultConfig()` 默认值\n150: - [ ] 7.3 测试 `TestParseFlags_CustomValues`：设置全部 18 个 flag → Config 字段完全匹配\n151: - [ ] 7.4 测试 `TestParseFlags_EnvOverrides`：设置环境变量（`ROUTER_PORT`, `ROUTER_DEBUG`, `ROUTER_STORE_TYPE` 等）→ 覆盖默认值\n152: - [ ] 7.5 测试 `TestParseFlags_TLSConfig`：`--enable-tls --tls-cert=/tmp/cert.pem --tls-key=/tmp/key.pem` → `EnableTLS=true`, `TLSCert` 和 `TLSKey` 正确填充\n153: - [ ] 7.6 测试 `TestParseFlags_JWTConfig`：`--jwt-expiration=10m --jwt-issuer=test --jwt-leeway=30s` → 对应 duration 和 issuer 正确\n154: - [ ] 7.7 测试 `TestParseFlags_HelpOutput`：`--help` 输出包含全部 18 个 flag 名称（覆盖 delta-spec router help output 场景）\n155: - [ ] 7.8 测试 `TestParseFlags_DurationParsing`：多个 duration flag 正确解析\n156: \n157: **Verification:** `go test ./cmd/router/... -v -count=1` 全部通过；覆盖 delta-spec §Requirement: router help output 场景\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## T8. 构建验证 — 全部 4 个二进制编译\n162: \n163: - [ ] 8.1 运行 `go build ./cmd/...` 确认全部 4 个二进制编译通过\n164: - [ ] 8.2 运行 `go build -o /dev/null ./cmd/agentd` 确认 agentd 二进制产出\n165: - [ ] 8.3 运行 `go build -o /dev/null ./cmd/picod` 确认 picod 二进制产出\n166: - [ ] 8.4 运行 `go build -o /dev/null ./cmd/workloadmanager` 确认 workloadmanager 二进制产出\n167: - [ ] 8.5 运行 `go build -o /dev/null ./cmd/router` 确认 router 二进制产出\n168: - [ ] 8.6 确认 `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` ≤ 100 行（设计门禁要求）\n169: - [ ] 8.7 确认 `cmd/router/main.go` ≤ 100 行（设计门禁要求）\n170: \n171: **Verification:** `go build ./cmd/...` exit 0；4 个二进制均可独立编译；两个新 main.go 行数 ≤ 100\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## T9. 代码质量门禁\n176: \n177: - [ ] 9.1 运行 `go vet ./cmd/...` 确认无警告\n178: - [ ] 9.2 运行 `go test ./cmd/... -v -count=1` 确认全部测试通过\n179: - [ ] 9.3 运行 `go test -race ./cmd/...` 确认无数据竞争\n180: - [ ] 9.4 运行 `go mod tidy` 确认无变更\n181: - [ ] 9.5 确认 `cmd/workloadmanager/` 下每个 `*.go` 文件都有对应的 `*_test.go` 文件\n182: - [ ] 9.6 确认 `cmd/router/` 下每个 `*.go` 文件都有对应的 `*_test.go` 文件\n183: - [ ] 9.7 确认无 `log.Printf` 使用（仅使用 `klog`）\n184: \n185: **Verification:** 以上 7 项全部通过；exit code 均为 0\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Task Dependencies\n190: \n191: ```\n192: T1 (确认现有二进制) ──────────────────────────────────┐\n193:                                                       │\n194: T2 (wm config) ──→ T3 (wm main) ──┐                   │\n195:                                    │                   │\n196: T4 (router config) ──→ T5 (router main) ─┐             │\n197:                                           │             │\n198: T6 (wm tests) ────────────────────────────┤             │\n199:                                           │             │\n200: T7 (router tests) ────────────────────────┤             │\n201:                                           │             │\n202:                                           ├──→ T8 (构建验证)\n203:                                           │      │\n204:                                           └──────┼────→ T9 (质量门禁)\n205:                                                  │\n206: T1 ──────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n207: ```\n208: \n209: **Parallel execution:**\n210: - T1（确认现有二进制）可独立执行，不阻塞其他任务\n211: - T2（wm config）和 T4（router config）可并行开发\n212: - T3（wm main）需 T2 完成后开始\n213: - T5（router main）需 T4 完成后开始\n214: - T6（wm tests）需 T2 完成后可开始（测试 flag 解析无需 main.go）\n215: - T7（router tests）需 T4 完成后可开始\n216: - T8（构建验证）需 T1、T3、T5 完成后开始\n217: - T9 为最终门禁，需所有前置任务完成\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Acceptance Criteria\n222: \n223: | # | Criterion | Command |\n224: |---|-----------|---------|\n225: | AC1 | 全部 4 个二进制编译通过 | `go build ./cmd/...` |\n226: | AC2 | agentd 编译通过 | `go build ./cmd/agentd` |\n227: | AC3 | picod 编译通过 | `go build ./cmd/picod` |\n228: | AC4 | workloadmanager 编译通过 | `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager` |\n229: | AC5 | router 编译通过 | `go build ./cmd/router` |\n230: | AC6 | workloadmanager flag 解析测试通过 | `go test ./cmd/workloadmanager/... -v` |\n231: | AC7 | router flag 解析测试通过 | `go test ./cmd/router/... -v` |\n232: | AC8 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./cmd/...` |\n233: | AC9 | 无 vet 警告 | `go vet ./cmd/...` |\n234: | AC10 | 依赖清理 | `go mod tidy` 无变更 |\n235: | AC11 | workloadmanager main.go ≤ 100 行 | `wc -l cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` |\n236: | AC12 | router main.go ≤ 100 行 | `wc -l cmd/router/main.go` |\n237: | AC13 | workloadmanager help 输出包含全部 flag | `go run ./cmd/workloadmanager -help 2>&1 \\| grep -c '\\-\\-'` ≥ 14 |\n238: | AC14 | router help 输出包含全部 flag | `go run ./cmd/router -help 2>&1 \\| grep -c '\\-\\-'` ≥ 18 |\n239: | AC15 | 每个源文件有对应测试文件 | `ls cmd/workloadmanager/*_test.go cmd/router/*_test.go` |\n240: | AC16 | 无 `log.Printf` 使用 | `grep -r 'log\\.Printf' cmd/` 无输出 |\n\n(End of file - total 240 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-019/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-019/design.md`, `changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. 确认现有二进制 — cmd/agentd 和 cmd/picod 无变更\n\n- [ ] 1.1 审查 `cmd/agentd/main.go`（59 行）确认已满足 delta-spec 中 agentd 的全部场景\n- [ ] 1.2 审查 `cmd/picod/main.go`（15 行）确认已满足 delta-spec 中 picod 的全部场景\n- [ ] 1.3 运行 `go build ./cmd/agentd ./cmd/picod` 确认两个现有二进制编译通过\n- [ ] 1.4 记录 agentd 的 flag（`--kubeconfig`, `--master`）和 picod 的 flag（通过 `picod.ParseFlags()`）\n\n**Verification:** `go build ./cmd/agentd ./cmd/picod` exit 0；两个 main.go 文件无内容变更\n\n---\n\n## T2. 实现 workloadmanager CLI 配置解析 — cmd/workloadmanager/config.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849597429,"end":1775849597436}}}}
